JOHANNESBURG - The South African Rugby Union has confirmed that Spingbok fly half Elton Jantjies was arrested at OR Tambo International Airport. The 31-year-old was handcuffed on his arrival in Johannesburg from Dubai on Sunday morning. Gauteng police said they arrested him for damaging property on a flight and he was escorted off the plane by law enforcement officials. Saru President Mark Alexander said they have been made aware of the arrest.